parameters:
Glasses Kid: Hey! Benji! How long are you going to
pee for!

The man at dusk sighed, Ah... It's been warm and
pleasant lately...

Running Woman: Hah... hah... hah... Just 3... 4...
no, let's make it 5 more weeks!

Troubled student: Damn it... I can't extend my
time... What should I do...

It seems like you're troubled about something...
Should I try talking to you?

Akira: Ah, Ayako-san! Um... would you run with me
again?!

(W-What's wrong...? The pressure is intense...
Should I run together with them...?)
I'm sorry... I have something to take care of...

(I'm feeling really down... I guess it's because
of what happened last time...)

(If things continue like this, it might affect the
tournament... I have to find a way to cheer them
up...!)

Akira: Ayako-san!! I've been waiting! Please tell
me the results!

(I guess I have no choice but to listen to what
you have to say.)

This event requires a lewdness level of 200 or
higher.

Akira: Hehehe...! Ayako-san!! Today, I'm a bit
different from usual...!!

Akira: The answer I couldn't ask you last time...!
Today, I'll definitely make you tell me...!

(I-I'm filled with confidence... It seems like
something happened...)

(I have to give a clear answer... What should I
do...?)
(L-Let me take a deep breath for a moment...!)

After the event ends, if you press the Q key, you
can hear Ayako's soliloquy about that event.

Basically, it doesn't affect the game progress if
you don't listen to it, but she might whisper
something that could lead to hints for capturing.

Also, be aware that if you fall asleep at home or
listen to the event-related soliloquy
once,\c[2]she won't whisper it again.\c[0] So
please be careful if you want to hear all the
conversations.

Hmm... Rei-san said it was a 'single bill', but
this one isn't sparkling, so maybe it's
different...

Let's try looking for anything else that might
have fallen.

...It's sparkling and there are lots of words
written like spells! But... it's not a bill, just
a regular notebook that you can buy...

Hmm, I can't quite put my finger on it... Is this
even the right place where I dropped it?
Rei-san... you're so carefree, aren't you...
Let's try searching a little longer.

Ah, a really sparkling thing fell! This time for
sure...!
I obtained an Ultra Rare Card!

This must be it! The picture is sparkling, and
there are lots of words. It even says 'One Card'!
Yes! Let's take it to Rei-san!
